<div style="background-color:#7c7c7c; color:white; padding:20px; font-size:22px; margin-left:20px;">2. DIFFERENT NUMBERS</div>

<div style="background-color:#b8b8b8; color:white; padding:20px; font-size:22px; margin-left:20px; line-height:150%;">Please explain the different numbers that I received?</div>

<ul class="indiFAQ">
<li style="padding:0px 20px 0px 0px; font-family:arial; font-size:14px; line-height:150%;">One number is your Agreement number - this number is alpha-numeric ,<br />e.g. IM4924</li>
<li style="padding:0px 20px 0px 0px; font-family:arial; font-size:14px; line-height:150%;">One number is your Quality Vacation Club membership number - this number is also alpha-numeric, e.g. QVC 1234</li>
<li style="padding:0px 20px 0px 0px; font-family:arial; font-size:14px; line-height:150%;">One number is your RCI number - this number is also alpha-numeric, e.g. QVCL -2354 or UNVS 12345</li>
<li style="padding:0px 20px 0px 0px; font-family:arial; font-size:14px; line-height:150%;">One number is your Management Fee number – this number is also alpha-numeric, e.g. LQVC 1234</li>
<li style="padding:0px 20px 0px 0px; font-family:arial; font-size:14px; line-height:150%;">One number is your Nox insurance number – tis number is also alpha-numeric,<br />e.g. NOX 1234</li>
</ul>
